The paper deals with the theory of concurrency and languages generated by bi-Kleene operations, which are topics typically studied in the sub-fields of logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses completeness theorems, which are often studied in theoretical computer science (cs.THEORY).
